article.headline: Glasper, Shell rally North Carolina A&T to 81-80 victory over Hampton
article.description: — Landon Glasper scored 24 points and Camian Shell hit the game-winning jump shot with two seconds remaining as the Aggies knocked off Hampton 81-80 on Monday night.
article.linkText: Glasper, Shell rally North Carolina A&T to 81-80 victory over Hampton
article.story: HAMPTON, Va. -- — Landon Glasper scored 24 points and Camian Shell hit the game-winning jump shot with two seconds remaining as the Aggies knocked off Hampton 81-80 on Monday night. Glasper also contributed eight rebounds for the Aggies (4-13, 2-2 Coastal Athletic Association). Shell scored 19 points and added eight assists. Nikolaos Chitikoudis had 15 points and shot 7 of 9 from the field. Jordan Nesbitt led the Pirates (4-13, 0-5) in scoring, finishing with 17 points and five assists. Jerry Deng added 17 points for Hampton. Tristan Maxwell also had 12 points. The Pirates extended their losing streak to eight in a row. N.C. A&T went into the half tied with Hampton 42-42. Shell scored 11 points in the half. Glasper led N.C. A&T with 13 points in the second half. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
